Because LibreOffice compatibility matters, I should avoid Excel 365-only functions like `TEXTSPLIT`. A compatible approach is a `SUMPRODUCT` formula that checks whether each `Data!C` truck number appears as a whole token within the comma-separated list in `Report!C`, after removing spaces and padding commas. It should also work when `Report!C` is a single numeric truck ID.

Next I’ll inspect exact rows/cells and then write formulas into the blank result cells (and likely all report data rows for consistency), save to the output path, recalculate if possible, and verify the results.
Code:
